sec.p:
There have been several attempts to create a unified standard for instant messaging: IETF's SIP (
Session Initiation Protocol
) and SIMPLE ( SIP for Instant Messaging and Presence Leveraging Extensions), APEX (
Application Exchange
), Prim (Presence and Instant Messaging Protocol), the open XML-based XMPP ( Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol), more commonly known as Jabber and OMA's ( Open Mobile Alliance) IMPS ( Instant Messaging and Presence Service) created specifically for mobile devices.

